plan_moves.prompt:
Your name is agent_1.
Public information:
{environment->public_information}
Your private information:
{agents->agent_1->private_information}
Global goal:
{agents->agent_1->goal}
Produce an ordered list (one move per line) of primitive moves you will perform. Each move must exactly follow the format 'agent_1: move disk X from pegY to pegZ'. Keep moves legal and only for disks A-J.

Your name is agent_2.
Public information:
{environment->public_information}
Your private information:
{agents->agent_2->private_information}
Global goal:
{agents->agent_2->goal}
Produce an ordered list (one move per line) of primitive moves you will perform. Each move must exactly follow the format 'agent_2: move disk X from pegY to pegZ'. Keep moves legal and only for disks K-T.

pddl.prompt:
You are orchestrator.
You will receive the agents' move lists:
{moves_agent_1}
{moves_agent_2}
Integrate them into one valid, fully ordered move sequence that reaches the stated goal.
Then produce a PDDL domain and problem suitable for FastDownward that represents the instance (20 disks, 3 pegs), the allowed agent-specific move actions, the initial state, and the goal state. Enclose domain with <domain></domain> and problem with <problem></problem> tags. Also include the final ordered move list (one move per line) immediately before the PDDL tags.
